00:20:26,340 --> 00:20:31,420
Alfred, she is adorable.
Get back to those potatoes.

235
00:20:37,020 --> 00:20:41,220
-What song did my mom suggest?
-Something personal and timeless.

236
00:20:41,420 --> 00:20:42,820
-A classic.
-So...

237
00:20:43,020 --> 00:20:46,740
-"You Can Be My Bitch", by Master B?
-The live version or radio edit?

238
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:49,500
Live, since he burns the stage down
and starts a riot.

239
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:51,900
Nice.
Very nice.

240
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:58,300
-How about "Endless Love"?
-Doesn't one of them die in the end?

241
00:20:59,620 --> 00:21:01,500
Good point.

242
00:21:04,140 --> 00:21:06,940
-I've got it.
-What?

243
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:14,820
A little soul
is necessary in life.

244
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:44,580
Excuse me.

245
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:28,500
-Stick with the painting thing, please.
-Sometimes you just got to loosen up.

246
00:22:31,380 --> 00:22:33,940
Can't be an old man.

247
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:40,980
You rock!

248
00:22:41,420 --> 00:22:43,580
You know, I taught her that.

249
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:48,180
All right, maybe I had
to loosen up a little.

250
00:22:48,380 --> 00:22:52,260
So I volunteered
for her art project.

251
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:56,860
-This sucks.
-Don't move an inch.

252
00:22:57,100 --> 00:23:00,860
-You're really enjoying this, aren't you?
-More than you know.

253
00:23:05,380 --> 00:23:08,060
As you've heard many times
before right here...

254
00:23:08,260 --> 00:23:11,900
you're not prepared to cook vegetables
unless you're prepared to pick them.

255
00:23:12,060 --> 00:23:16,500
You don' t just ask anybody to dance.
You ask the girl that looks good to you.

256
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:19,860
Now, what's wrong
with this picture?

257
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:23,140
This lady has had
a night of self-indulgence.

258
00:23:23,540 --> 00:23:25,460
You don't take her home
to your mom.

259
00:23:26,420 --> 00:23:30,940
This is perfection.
"P" for perfect.

260
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:33,500
No detergents
smelling up her aroma.

261
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:36,260
No bruises shading her figure.

262
00:23:36,660 --> 00:23:39,900
No, this is perfect. Wait!
Where is Al?

263
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:42,180
Alfred?

264
00:23:43,220 --> 00:23:46,940
There he is. Al, my son.
Al, come out here. Come on.

265
00:23:47,140 --> 00:23:49,820
Don't dawdle. These people
have got places do go.

266
00:23:50,060 --> 00:23:51,780
My son, Al,
ladies and gentlemen.

267
00:23:54,780 --> 00:23:58,460
He's going to be a chef too.
He's so cute.

268
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:03,100
Feel that. You tell me,
is that perfection?

269
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:05,780
Yeah, it's pretty ripe.

270
00:24:07,460 --> 00:24:09,500
Al knows how to pick perfection.
How do I know?

271
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:14,780
Because she's in the audience
right now. And she is a tomato.

272
00:24:14,940 --> 00:24:18,940
Imogen. I said it right this time.
Stand up, honey.

273
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:23,100
Stand up. Come on.
There she is.

274
00:24:25,260 --> 00:24:28,260
-Say hello to your parents.
-Hi.

275
00:24:28,460 --> 00:24:33,140
-Did you pick perfection or what?
-Yeah, dad. She's perfect for me.

276
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:52,340
When you're falling in love, sometimes
one night makes it complete.

277
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:54,780
In our case, it was my birthday.

278
00:24:57,340 --> 00:25:00,020
Imogen went all out.

279
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:10,660
"Find the other candle."

280
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:13,340
The other candle?

281
00:25:37,580 --> 00:25:39,740
Happy birthday.

282
00:26:00,380 --> 00:26:02,860
-You look...
-You like?

283
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:07,780
-I like it a lot.
-Good.

284
00:26:08,060 --> 00:26:11,940
-Where are we?
-I wanted this night to be special.

285
00:26:12,140 --> 00:26:15,660
I wanted to share something that's
important to me with you.

286
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:19,100
This is my favorite place
in New York. I come here a lot...

287
00:26:19,260 --> 00:26:22,980
if I'm feeling down or homesick,
or if I just need a little inspiration.

288
00:26:23,180 --> 00:26:25,260
This place has real soul.

289
00:26:25,460 --> 00:26:29,260
It's not like those cheesy art galleries
which have T-shirts and postcards.

290
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:31,380
This is why I want
to be an artist.

291
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:34,940
Here, come on.

292
00:26:36,380 --> 00:26:38,580
They're all so beautiful.

293
00:26:38,780 --> 00:26:42,940
I don't know much about art.
I kind of stopped with finger-painting.

294
00:26:43,140 --> 00:26:46,620
But I like this...

295
00:26:47,420 --> 00:26:50,740
...blurry one.
-It's impressionistic.

296
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:54,100
It's not about how you see the world.
It's how the artist sees it.

297
00:26:54,540 --> 00:26:57,420
It's somehow completely personal.

298
00:26:58,380 --> 00:27:00,460
What do you see in this?

299
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:06,220
-Morning?
-Morning.

300
00:27:06,620 --> 00:27:11,660
Well, yeah. See, because all the
colors, the oranges and yellows...

301
00:27:11,860 --> 00:27:15,420
it kinda reminds me of
two people having eggs.

302
00:27:16,980 --> 00:27:19,740
-I don' t know.
-Do you see what the artist did...

303
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,940
with the way the colors
blend with the light?

304
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:25,220
And the brush technique says
something about the ambiance.

305
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:28,660
It sets a mood with
its luminous tones...

306
00:27:29,420 --> 00:27:32,940
and brilliant colors.
It's really just a moment captured...

307
00:27:33,180 --> 00:27:35,500
but in away that
makes it feel...

308
00:27:36,180 --> 00:27:37,980
alive.

309
00:27:41,340 --> 00:27:44,180
You make me feel alive.

310
00:27:55,260 --> 00:27:58,500
This is the best birthday
I've ever had.

311
00:27:59,100 --> 00:28:01,340
There's more upstairs.

312
00:28:30,460 --> 00:28:32,540
I'm falling in love with you.

313
00:28:35,740 --> 00:28:38,420
I love you.

314
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:49,260
-What about foreplay?
-We've had it for 3 months. Relax.

315
00:28:53,060 --> 00:28:56,980
It'll never be that
fast again. I promise.

316
00:29:01,540 --> 00:29:04,100
Look, I was really nervous
that first night...

317
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:06,900
but I think I more than made up
for it the second time.

318
00:29:07,100 --> 00:29:09,060
He really did make up for it.

319
00:29:09,260 --> 00:29:11,500
And the cake was
a perfect encore.

320
00:29:12,220 --> 00:29:14,340
She used to do
the cutest things...

321
00:29:14,540 --> 00:29:17,980
Like scratching my stomach
when she wanted it in the morning.

322
00:29:20,860 --> 00:29:24,140
Understandably, we'd have to keep
our faces from each other.

323
00:29:24,660 --> 00:29:26,820
Morning breath is a killer.

324
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:33,740
Of course, when he wanted it
in the morning he wasn't so subtle.

325
00:29:39,420 --> 00:29:42,300
-But those were the best days.
-The honeymoon days...

326
00:29:42,500 --> 00:29:44,700
-Where nothing mattered.
-Nothing but us.

327
00:29:44,860 --> 00:29:46,780
But it wouldn't be long before
the year was over ...

328
00:29:46,980 --> 00:29:51,100
-I was going to France that summer.
-I told her it's only France, 3 months.

329
00:29:51,260 --> 00:29:53,940
-It wouldn't be so bad.
-I didn't want to leave.

330
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:57,620
I didn't want the year to end.
It was the best year of my life.

331
00:29:57,820 --> 00:30:00,180
I'm in love.

332
00:30:02,460 --> 00:30:07,260
-Tingles and everything?
-Yeah, tingles and everything.

333
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:12,420
Love is a hoax. Our emotions are
all provoked by chemical reactions.

334
00:30:12,620 --> 00:30:15,220
It creates this euphoria
that makes you stupid.

335
00:30:16,180 --> 00:30:19,940
It's all biochemistry. Trust me.
It was my major.

336
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:24,060
I'm afraid it's true, Al.
All romantics are simply addicts.

337
00:30:24,380 --> 00:30:27,740
You guys just need to experience
something of substance.

338
00:30:27,900 --> 00:30:30,460
-Then you'll know my language.
-Prove this love.

339
00:30:30,660 --> 00:30:33,740
You speak of its power.
Why not show us?

340
00:30:35,820 --> 00:30:39,900
One of these is love,
the other, illusion.

341
00:30:40,660 --> 00:30:43,980
Drink each and choose,
but choose wisely...

342
00:30:44,180 --> 00:30:46,460
for there is no second chance.

343
00:30:46,620 --> 00:30:49,020
You cannot have a test
without a wager.

344
00:30:50,380 --> 00:30:52,180
Point taken.

345
00:30:52,380 --> 00:30:56,540
If you fail, you have to be an extra
in the picture tomorrow night.

346
00:30:56,700 --> 00:30:58,820
-And if I win?
-Then I'll buy you...

347
00:30:59,020 --> 00:31:03,180
...an all-you-can-eat sushi dinner.
-I don't want all the sushi I can eat!

348
00:31:03,380 --> 00:31:06,220
Trust me, you will.
Now drink.

349
00:31:19,100 --> 00:31:21,340
Chop-chop.

350
00:31:30,380 --> 00:31:32,540
The second one.

351
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:36,660
-You're certain?
-I'm positive.

352
00:31:38,820 --> 00:31:42,300
This is love.
You chose illusion.

353
00:31:43,900 --> 00:31:47,580
I... I didn't.
It's love, I know it.

354
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:50,980
Call us at 9 PM, baby.
Be ready to shine.

355
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:53,780
There's a party in 4O6.
Want to go?

356
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:57,820
I'm your friend so it's my duty
to warn you.

357
00:31:58,020 --> 00:32:03,620
Soon those tingles will disappear
and you won't know what hit you.

358
00:32:13,020 --> 00:32:16,740
Actually, I'm not going
to be around tonight.

359
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:19,100
No? Why?

360
00:32:20,180 --> 00:32:23,300
I promised Monk I'd be en extra
in a film he's directing.

361
00:32:24,180 --> 00:32:25,980
What?

362
00:32:26,140 --> 00:32:28,820
I promised Monk I'd be an extra
in a film he's directing.

363
00:32:29,020 --> 00:32:33,500
-You'll be an extra in a porno movie?
-An epic. They reinvented the genre.

364
00:32:33,780 --> 00:32:35,780
-You're not going...
-No.

365
00:32:36,420 --> 00:32:39,580
Besides, they're
paying me fifty bucks.

366
00:32:39,780 --> 00:32:42,140
You'd rather be on
a movie set than...?

367
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:47,460
It's a battle scene and
the regular extras are on strike.

368
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:50,900
I'm leaving for France in two weeks
and instead of sleeping with me...

369
00:32:51,100 --> 00:32:53,820
you'd rather be a day-player
in some flick?

370
00:32:54,300 --> 00:32:58,860
-It's an extra. It's a pay difference.
-Fine. This way we have it.

371
00:32:59,060 --> 00:33:01,740
You can decide if we eat it too.

372
00:33:08,100 --> 00:33:09,980
Action!

373
00:33:23,380 --> 00:33:27,420
Watching Monk prepare to lead his
troops into battle, I kept wondering...

374
00:33:28,220 --> 00:33:33,180
what was I doing?
I chose this over Imogen?

375
00:33:38,740 --> 00:33:40,780
All I wanted to do was see her.

376
00:33:45,100 --> 00:33:47,340
To be with her.

377
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:45,540
When you have moments
like that one...

378
00:34:45,740 --> 00:34:48,660
you can't even imagine
it won't stay that way.

379
00:34:49,980 --> 00:34:52,180
Look at those two.

380
00:34:54,340 --> 00:34:56,900
They can't keep their hands
off each other.

381
00:34:57,100 --> 00:35:00,340
I'll bet you they think they'll
always be that happy.

382
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:04,460
I have some errands to run.

383
00:35:29,140 --> 00:35:33,700
So Imogen ended up going to France
for the summer.

384
00:35:33,980 --> 00:35:37,860
Remember how I told her it was just
France and three months?

385
00:35:38,300 --> 00:35:42,180
It turns out that whole distance thing
was a little harder than I thought.

386
00:36:27,820 --> 00:36:29,700
Welcome back.

387
00:36:45,820 --> 00:36:48,700
So, what do you think?

388
00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:52,220
Very beefy, Eddie.

389
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:57,820
-What's with the Mullet cut?
-This? It's pretty cool, right?

390
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:01,980
These are coming back.

391
00:37:03,180 --> 00:37:05,420
They are, just you wait.

392
00:37:20,940 --> 00:37:23,260
-Your eyes are open.
-So?

393
00:37:23,460 --> 00:37:27,100
-That's weird.
-Is it? Let me see.

394
00:37:28,900 --> 00:37:31,740
-That is weird.
-Too weird.

395
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:36,620
Why? Don't you want to watch me,
watch my eyes while I kiss you?

396
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:41,460
-Isn't it better with the eyes closed?
-It depends on your mood, I guess.

397
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:47,820
-Stop.
-Why?

398
00:37:48,020 --> 00:37:51,100
-What?
-I don't know.

399
00:37:51,260 --> 00:37:55,740
-You like it?
-I don't know, it's different.

400
00:38:08,060 --> 00:38:11,260
This needs to go upstairs
for approval.

401
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:15,220
So I'm in France for the summer. I've
spent summer there since I was a kid.

402
00:38:15,460 --> 00:38:19,460
I'm meeting my dad's relatives in Nice,
clubbing with friends in Saint-Tropez.

403
00:38:19,660 --> 00:38:23,100
I even took that funny-looking boat to
Corsica. I was having so much fun.

404
00:38:23,260 --> 00:38:25,020
Did I miss Al?
Absolutely.

405
00:38:25,180 --> 00:38:28,580
He was all I talked about with friends.
Then my cousin Maeva asked me:

406
00:38:29,980 --> 00:38:33,420
-And I said: "What?"
-Married. Are you going to be married?

407
00:38:33,620 --> 00:38:36,540
Of course not.
I'm only nineteen years old.

408
00:38:36,740 --> 00:38:41,620
So now I'm back and lying in his arms.
It's so nice to back in those arms.

409
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:46,540
We're kissing and all I could think of
was that word: married.

410
00:38:46,740 --> 00:38:49,340
And I started getting
really confused.

411
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:52,540
And my new room-mate
only offered, well...

412
00:38:53,380 --> 00:38:57,980
...other distractions.
-Put this on. It's a doobie cap.

413
00:38:58,180 --> 00:39:01,580
It, like, totally intensifies it.

414
00:39:02,420 --> 00:39:06,340
Like, the pores in your head...

415
00:39:06,540 --> 00:39:08,620
I don't know.

416
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:13,340
It just holds the smoke in your head
for, like, a lot longer.

417
00:39:14,780 --> 00:39:16,220
It's so right.

418
00:39:22,140 --> 00:39:26,180
Thank you.
I am so proud of you.

419
00:39:26,380 --> 00:39:28,980
You did such a great job
on the show.

420
00:39:29,180 --> 00:39:33,020
Everybody loves you.
You worked so hard.

421
00:39:33,460 --> 00:39:35,740
You're going to be a senior.

422
00:39:39,220 --> 00:39:40,900
So?

423
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:44,220
Don't you think you should get your
butt into gear? You have a future.

424
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:48,260
I plan on going to the French
Culinary Institute after I graduate.

425
00:39:48,540 --> 00:39:50,980
That's a very smart move.

426
00:39:51,180 --> 00:39:54,940
-I think I might have a smarter one.
-What?

427
00:39:55,740 --> 00:39:58,220
I think we should do a show together.
Don't you think...

428
00:39:58,420 --> 00:40:00,980
a father and son show
would be a great hook?

429
00:40:01,180 --> 00:40:04,300
-What is it?
-You watch TV, right?

430
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:07,260
-What kind of shows do you watch?
-Talk-shows.

431
00:40:07,420 --> 00:40:08,940
Right, what else?

432
00:40:10,100 --> 00:40:11,820
-Enjoy it.
-"Cops".

433
00:40:12,060 --> 00:40:15,620
So I say we do a reality
cooking show.

434
00:40:17,060 --> 00:40:18,580
Explain.

435
00:40:19,060 --> 00:40:22,340
Are you sitting down?
It's called "Cooks".

436
00:40:22,740 --> 00:40:25,340
Now, imagine a truck, a big rig.

437
00:40:25,500 --> 00:40:28,820
And it is stock piled with food
and wines and spices.

438
00:40:29,020 --> 00:40:31,220
We travel around the country,
just you and me.

439
00:40:31,460 --> 00:40:34,740
I do the driving.
I call the shots.

440
00:40:34,900 --> 00:40:38,780
We drive all over the country and we
come to homes. Average homes.

441
00:40:40,540 --> 00:40:41,940
Go! Go! Go!

442
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:45,740
At the homes we rush in and say:
"We're going to make you dinner."

443
00:40:45,940 --> 00:40:49,540
We use the exciting style of all those
shows. Shaky camera and everything.

444
00:40:49,740 --> 00:40:53,540
We've got a SWAT guy hold the mat
gun point so they can't runaway.

445
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:58,380
While we're in the kitchen, we say:
"What kind of meal would you like?"

446
00:40:58,580 --> 00:41:01,180
-Chateaubriand?
-And then we cook.

447
00:41:01,340 --> 00:41:03,740
But while we're cooking,
we teach.

448
00:41:04,060 --> 00:41:06,140
-If we need something special...
-Garlic!

449
00:41:06,460 --> 00:41:11,020
...a meat, a fish, a cheese, everyone
likes cheese... you got the truck.

450
00:41:11,220 --> 00:41:12,460
It's bread!

451
00:41:12,660 --> 00:41:14,940
Every week a new cuisine.
Every week...

452
00:41:15,140 --> 00:41:18,740
a new home.
What do you think?

453
00:41:19,900 --> 00:41:23,460
-Sounds like a winner, Dad.
-What's wrong?

454
00:41:29,460 --> 00:41:32,380
-Imogen.
-No.

455
00:41:36,500 --> 00:41:40,420
Things locked inside become cancer.
Do you know what a cancer does?

456
00:41:40,620 --> 00:41:44,940
Costs a lot of money to treat.
I'm sorry. It's just...

457
00:41:45,500 --> 00:41:48,940
she's been back awhile now
and it's not the same.

458
00:41:49,220 --> 00:41:52,180
It's all about growing up
and growing together.

459
00:41:52,380 --> 00:41:55,540
It's all about growing old
and growing apart.

460
00:41:55,740 --> 00:42:01,500
Excuse me. It takes work, Al. So,
either you do the work or you get out.

461
00:42:13,420 --> 00:42:15,420
That one's no good.

462
00:42:19,860 --> 00:42:23,740
When guys drift from their loved ones
they sometimes drift toward...

463
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:26,940
how should I put this?
Less productive pursuits.

464
00:42:34,620 --> 00:42:36,380
What's up?

465
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:39,820
Monk called.
Having people over.

466
00:42:40,020 --> 00:42:42,460
I got a mid-term in the morning.

467
00:42:46,260 --> 00:42:50,660
-He left this for you.
-You're lame, man.

468
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:56,220
Don't mess with these guns!
