So I decided to date again.

704
01:04:32,660 --> 01:04:37,380
I only allow myself to have crabs on
weekends. So thank God it's Friday.

705
01:04:38,540 --> 01:04:40,500
Are you going to eat your bread?

706
01:04:41,380 --> 01:04:46,020
He's cute and he didn't bring me
to a cheap restaurant. Okay. Bye.

707
01:04:46,500 --> 01:04:48,500
My dad.
He just likes to check in.

708
01:04:50,580 --> 01:04:54,780
State requires that I wear a tracking
device or I violate my parole.

709
01:04:57,660 --> 01:05:02,460
I know this is a little bit silly,
but do I have any food in my teeth?

710
01:05:03,420 --> 01:05:06,820
As you can see,
my choices were limited.

711
01:05:07,020 --> 01:05:11,220
So one day I bumped into Cyrus
and we started having a fling.

712
01:05:11,860 --> 01:05:16,340
Trouble is she had this thing
about Barnes and Noble bookstores.

713
01:05:17,980 --> 01:05:20,900
But I could never bring myself
to make her pancakes.

714
01:05:22,940 --> 01:05:25,380
I heard she went back to MIT.

715
01:05:25,780 --> 01:05:28,700
So, I thought going to the Culinary
Institute would turn my life around.

716
01:05:32,060 --> 01:05:35,260
But food never tasted
like it used to do.

717
01:05:36,740 --> 01:05:38,860
I started cutting class.

718
01:05:39,860 --> 01:05:42,980
I flunked the pop quiz
on fish fileting.

719
01:05:43,260 --> 01:05:47,060
And pretty soon
I was a culinary drop-out.

720
01:05:50,580 --> 01:05:54,820
With nothing else to do, I was forced
to go bar-hopping with Hicks.

721
01:06:00,540 --> 01:06:03,180
I'd sure like to unfold
her napkin, you know?

722
01:06:05,300 --> 01:06:09,300
-God, I'm feeling grabby tonight.
-Last night wasn't enough?

723
01:06:10,740 --> 01:06:12,900
I didn't arrive.

724
01:06:13,460 --> 01:06:17,660
-You didn't arrive?
-No, I was too wasted.

725
01:06:17,860 --> 01:06:20,900
-Was she older or younger?
-Sixty.

726
01:06:21,220 --> 01:06:25,820
-You slept with a 6O-year old woman?
-When you work in physical therapy...

727
01:06:26,020 --> 01:06:30,020
...you make friends fast.
-My God.

728
01:06:30,660 --> 01:06:32,420
-I'm not interested anymore...
-No way!

729
01:06:32,580 --> 01:06:34,940
It's just what I need.

730
01:06:35,300 --> 01:06:38,340
-The economy catch.
-It was your idea, damn it!

731
01:06:38,540 --> 01:06:40,660
She's with a guy.

732
01:06:40,860 --> 01:06:43,020
-But they are fighting, Al.
-Go!

733
01:06:43,500 --> 01:06:45,580
They are fighting.

734
01:06:48,180 --> 01:06:50,900
'Sup?'sup?

735
01:06:52,340 --> 01:06:54,900
You want some of this?

736
01:06:55,100 --> 01:06:57,500
Get the hell out of here!

737
01:07:10,820 --> 01:07:13,380
I had moved into
my own little studio.

738
01:07:16,660 --> 01:07:19,700
I stood there wondering where
she was at that moment...

739
01:07:20,220 --> 01:07:23,940
what she was doing.
How did her hair look?

740
01:07:24,740 --> 01:07:26,940
I just wanted to see her again.

741
01:07:28,740 --> 01:07:31,140
I'd saved all these things
from our past.

742
01:07:31,620 --> 01:07:36,100
Letters, tapes we made
to each other, pictures.

743
01:07:36,420 --> 01:07:39,100
I just wanted to look
through it all again.

744
01:07:39,300 --> 01:07:42,420
Remember it.
Remember her.

745
01:07:45,380 --> 01:07:50,020
When I was thru, instead of feeling like
I could shake things off and move on...

746
01:07:50,540 --> 01:07:52,980
I felt the opposite.

747
01:08:41,740 --> 01:08:44,580
We can do silly things for love.

748
01:08:46,580 --> 01:08:49,820
You wouldn't believe what I did.

749
01:08:51,820 --> 01:08:55,060
Luckily he had a phenomenal amount
of alcohol in his blood...

750
01:08:55,260 --> 01:08:57,940
which kept the shampoo from circulating
before we could get it out of him.

751
01:08:58,140 --> 01:09:00,180
Shampoo?

752
01:09:00,380 --> 01:09:04,020
We're gonna have a psych evaluate
him. Maybe we'll get some answers.

753
01:09:05,060 --> 01:09:07,460
-Can we see him?
-Sure.

754
01:09:07,980 --> 01:09:10,660
Come on. Shampoo?

755
01:09:20,620 --> 01:09:22,900
-What did you do?
-We were worried sick.

756
01:09:23,100 --> 01:09:26,260
-Look what you put your mother through!
-They want a psych to check you out.

757
01:09:26,500 --> 01:09:29,260
Mom, Dad, stop.

758
01:09:30,260 --> 01:09:32,500
I'm okay.

759
01:09:33,860 --> 01:09:35,620
Yes, you are.

760
01:09:35,820 --> 01:09:39,340
So why don't you tell us
about this shampoo thing?

761
01:09:40,020 --> 01:09:43,900
You drank the shampoo because
you hoped you were immune to it?

762
01:09:44,260 --> 01:09:46,180
-Right.
-You hoped you were immune to it?

763
01:09:46,380 --> 01:09:48,780
-The shampoo.
-Why did you hope you were immune?

764
01:09:49,140 --> 01:09:53,060
Because if I was immune to it
then I wouldn't need it again ever.

765
01:09:53,220 --> 01:09:55,140
-The shampoo?
-No, her.

766
01:09:55,460 --> 01:09:58,060
But you weren't immune to it. You
needed to have your stomach pumped.

767
01:09:59,300 --> 01:10:03,300
-That's what worries me.
-When was the last time you saw her?

768
01:10:03,460 --> 01:10:06,820
It's been a while.
She moved out west to start over.

769
01:10:07,020 --> 01:10:09,700
I found out she's working for
a publishing company, doing artwork.

770
01:10:09,860 --> 01:10:12,740
Have you had any
girlfriends since?

771
01:10:17,780 --> 01:10:23,340
That's my number. From the sound of
all this, I think I found my next book.

772
01:10:25,420 --> 01:10:29,740
-How are you feeling?
-Pumping me with garlic and olive oil.

773
01:10:30,020 --> 01:10:33,620
-What are you going to do next?
-I was thinking about...

774
01:10:34,140 --> 01:10:36,700
giving Paul John Breslin
at Oceana a call.

775
01:10:36,900 --> 01:10:41,300
Oceana? He's a Mussolini. Why not
just go dry dishes somewhere?

776
01:10:41,500 --> 01:10:44,180
-You don't need that.
-Dad, I do need that.

777
01:10:46,500 --> 01:10:48,900
I wasn't going to tell you this
until you were better.

778
01:10:49,220 --> 01:10:53,500
You know our show, "Cooks"?
It's been approved.

779
01:10:53,700 --> 01:10:56,260
We can do it the way
we talked about it.

780
01:10:56,900 --> 01:11:01,460
Dad, I kinda wanna work my way up.
"Cooks" is your thing.

781
01:11:04,100 --> 01:11:06,980
You know, sometimes I don't even
know if you're making sense.

782
01:11:07,260 --> 01:11:09,300
Dad.

783
01:11:09,860 --> 01:11:11,740
I know what I need to do.

784
01:11:17,140 --> 01:11:21,260
I was thinking about having
this party for you, for the show.

785
01:11:21,820 --> 01:11:23,500
Maybe we should have it anyway.

786
01:11:23,780 --> 01:11:27,780
You can invite all your friends.
We'll have fun.

787
01:11:30,260 --> 01:11:32,420
No shampoo.

788
01:11:48,820 --> 01:11:52,300
-Excellent choice.
-I knew you'd approve.

789
01:11:52,500 --> 01:11:55,340
-Always.
-Remember the first time we heard it?

790
01:11:55,540 --> 01:11:57,420
I do.

791
01:12:01,420 --> 01:12:03,940
I would like you to meet Emma.

792
01:12:07,500 --> 01:12:12,380
Sorry we didn't meet at the club, but
I was busy looking to take Eddie home.

793
01:12:15,900 --> 01:12:20,860
We had ice-cream and
he listened to my problems...

794
01:12:21,060 --> 01:12:24,260
and then we fell asleep
in each other's arms.

795
01:12:25,020 --> 01:12:26,940
We...

796
01:12:27,460 --> 01:12:29,380
kind of hit it off.

797
01:12:29,860 --> 01:12:32,540
-That's really cool.
-Shit.

798
01:12:32,740 --> 01:12:34,900
We're going to miss Shark Week.

799
01:12:35,100 --> 01:12:38,020
She loves the Discovery Channel.
What can I tell you?

800
01:12:38,220 --> 01:12:41,740
-Let's take a cab, okay?
-No, subway is faster.

801
01:13:01,140 --> 01:13:04,180
I'm not good with open wounds.

802
01:13:05,300 --> 01:13:08,260
You were always my Lancelot.

803
01:13:08,460 --> 01:13:11,460
I was just never your king.

804
01:13:16,260 --> 01:13:19,140
A lot of good moments
in that park down there.

805
01:13:22,820 --> 01:13:25,260
How is the Renaissance?

806
01:13:25,580 --> 01:13:30,300
It's good. My new book
is out next month.

807
01:13:32,420 --> 01:13:36,780
I'm doing the university lecture
tour thing.

808
01:13:37,660 --> 01:13:41,220
The movies are always there,
always making money.

809
01:13:42,300 --> 01:13:47,780
But I'd only admit this to you.
I miss the tingles.

810
01:13:51,740 --> 01:13:54,460
I heard a rumor you tried to...

811
01:13:55,140 --> 01:13:57,580
end it.

812
01:13:58,260 --> 01:14:02,340
I tried to get my life back
through a...

813
01:14:02,500 --> 01:14:04,260
romantic exorcism.

814
01:14:05,380 --> 01:14:09,780
It's not the meaning of life, Alfred.
It's the feeling of life.

815
01:14:11,300 --> 01:14:14,220
Look at that park down there.

816
01:14:14,620 --> 01:14:18,660
Just think how many loves
lost and found in it.

817
01:14:18,860 --> 01:14:23,820
How many first kisses kissed.
Frisbees lost.

818
01:14:25,060 --> 01:14:27,140
And just remember...

819
01:14:28,380 --> 01:14:30,780
that's your park, friend.

820
01:14:32,460 --> 01:14:35,300
And you've got your whole life
to walk through it.

821
01:15:10,660 --> 01:15:15,260
I was in town so I called you at your
old number. It was disconnected.

822
01:15:16,740 --> 01:15:20,380
-I moved.
-I know. I called your parents.

823
01:15:20,580 --> 01:15:22,260
They filled me in.

824
01:15:38,820 --> 01:15:41,540
San Francisco seems
to agree with you.

825
01:15:42,060 --> 01:15:45,540
You even have a tinge
of Haigh-Ashbury.

826
01:15:45,740 --> 01:15:49,300
It's kinda hard to dodge that style
when you live in the Haigh.

827
01:15:50,140 --> 01:15:55,140
Must be nice, though. Having a job,
doing what you love.

828
01:15:55,340 --> 01:15:57,620
Sometimes I think it's silly.

829
01:15:57,820 --> 01:16:01,340
But then when I go to the bookstores
and I see the covers that I've done...

830
01:16:01,540 --> 01:16:06,100
-I don't know. It's kind of cool.
-It's really cool.

831
01:16:06,380 --> 01:16:10,020
I mean, they flew you out here
for a book convention...

832
01:16:10,180 --> 01:16:12,980
and put you up in a hotel
for the whole weekend.

833
01:16:13,220 --> 01:16:16,180
Sounds like you're doing
really well.

834
01:16:17,900 --> 01:16:19,660
So...

835
01:16:20,820 --> 01:16:23,140
you're going to work in fish.

836
01:16:24,260 --> 01:16:26,660
You know how I feel about fish.

837
01:16:40,580 --> 01:16:45,820
-That one has a really nice view.
-I've seen better.

838
01:17:10,820 --> 01:17:12,580
Megan, sweetie, come on.

839
01:17:15,900 --> 01:17:18,140
You know what my fear is?

840
01:17:18,340 --> 01:17:21,220
-What?
-One day we'll pass on the street...

841
01:17:21,380 --> 01:17:26,020
...and have an artificial conversation.
-That's the worst.

842
01:17:31,060 --> 01:17:34,020
So, you're going home tomorrow?

843
01:17:34,180 --> 01:17:38,700
Actually, today.
My flight is in two hours.

844
01:17:40,260 --> 01:17:42,180
The sun will be up soon.

845
01:17:42,380 --> 01:17:45,620
I can't believe we spent
the whole night walking around.

846
01:17:54,260 --> 01:17:58,060
-This looks familiar.
-I try to avoid this corner.

847
01:17:58,260 --> 01:18:01,340
Let's go over there. It'll help you
overcome your demons.

848
01:18:01,540 --> 01:18:04,540
-Now you're the therapist again.
-And you're the patient again.

849
01:18:04,740 --> 01:18:06,660
As always.

850
01:18:17,220 --> 01:18:20,780
So can I psychoanalyze you?

851
01:18:22,580 --> 01:18:24,740
Sure.

852
01:18:25,180 --> 01:18:28,020
Post-collegiate years:
half-empty or half-full?

853
01:18:28,300 --> 01:18:32,740
-Half-empty.
-I'd have to go with half-empty too.

854
01:18:34,100 --> 01:18:37,700
Greatest accomplishment
since I last saw you?

855
01:18:37,900 --> 01:18:40,620
Making friends with a spider.

856
01:18:42,980 --> 01:18:45,820
-Vices?
-Shampoo.

857
01:18:46,300 --> 01:18:48,940
Was that rumor true?

858
01:18:49,140 --> 01:18:51,780
It's open to interpretation.

859
01:18:53,740 --> 01:18:56,140
What are your vices?

860
01:18:56,340 --> 01:19:00,500
-It's supposed to be about you, not me.
-It's been about you a little bit.

861
01:19:01,460 --> 01:19:05,380
-The sun's going to come up soon.
-Don't change the subject.

862
01:19:11,140 --> 01:19:12,700
You.

863
01:19:13,900 --> 01:19:15,540
You mean that?

864
01:19:18,940 --> 01:19:20,980
I should go.

865
01:19:21,180 --> 01:19:24,020
I really should go.
My flight's in...

866
01:19:24,220 --> 01:19:27,940
I've gotta go to my hotel and get
my bags, and I'm gonna be late.

867
01:19:35,180 --> 01:19:36,860
Will I see you again?

868
01:19:41,500 --> 01:19:45,500
Just open it after I leave.

869
01:20:53,460 --> 01:20:56,180
How can this work?

870
01:20:56,380 --> 01:20:58,300
I don't know.

871
01:20:58,820 --> 01:21:02,740
-But we've come this far.
-I thought we met too young.

872
01:21:03,500 --> 01:21:06,460
But in starting over we could get
some place different.

873
01:21:07,940 --> 01:21:10,260
Some place we never imagined.

874
01:21:29,540 --> 01:21:32,300
Al was right.
We met too young.

875
01:21:32,500 --> 01:21:35,180
But Imogen was right.
We could start over.

876
01:21:35,380 --> 01:21:39,060
-Starting over meant making choices.
-So I made one.

877
01:21:39,340 --> 01:21:41,900
I got a job at
a four-star restaurant...

878
01:21:42,100 --> 01:21:44,020
in San Francisco.

879
01:21:44,220 --> 01:21:46,060
-Now...
-I'm home.

880
01:21:46,260 --> 01:21:48,860
I had one thing left to prove.

881
01:22:03,500 --> 01:22:07,940
"Why are you walking around in
the dark? Go turn on the lights."

